African Union, U.K. Express ‘Deep Concern’ About Conflict in Ivory Coast

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-04-05T05:54:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/african-union-u-k-express-deep-concern-over-conflict-in-ivory-coast.html
African Union  Commission Chairman
Jean Ping and U.K. Foreign Secretary  William Hague  expressed
“deep concern” at the conflict in  Ivory Coast  that has led to
a “worsening humanitarian crisis.”  Ping and Hague called for restraint on all sides and for
civilians to be protected, according to an e-mailed statement
from the Addis Ababa-based African Union. Ping and Hague met in
 London  yesterday, the organization said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  